{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f6f39c4b-4321-48bd-9246-303397d5b688","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. Here's how to diagnose and configure on the machine where it's running:\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — Identify the runtime\n\n```bash\n# CoreCLR loads libcoreclr.so; NativeAOT does not\ncat /proc/12345/maps | grep -i coreclr\n```\n\n- **Output shows `libcoreclr.so`** → CoreCLR\n- **No output** → NativeAOT (self-contained, no CLR libs)\n\nYou can also check:\n```bash\n# NativeAOT binaries are statically linked and won't list coreclr\nldd /proc/12345/exe | grep -i coreclr\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Configure crash dumps\n\n#### If **CoreCLR**:\n\nSet environment variables (e.g. in a systemd unit or shell wrapper):\n\n```bash\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1          # enable automatic dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4            # 4 = Full heap dump (1=Mini, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n```\n\nAlso ensure the OS allows core dumps:\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n#### If **NativeAOT**:\n\nNativeAOT apps don't have the managed `DbgMiniDump` infrastructure. Use the **OS-level** core dump mechanism instead:\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# Set core dump pattern (system-wide, requires root)\necho '/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# Or use systemd-coredump (if available)\necho '|/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-coredump %P %u %g %s %t %c %h' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n```\n\nTo analyze NativeAOT dumps, use **`lldb`** (not `dotnet-dump`, which is CoreCLR-only):\n```bash\nlldb --core /tmp/dumps/core.myapp.12345 /path/to/myapp\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| Detection | `libcoreclr.so` in maps | No CLR libs loaded |\n| Dump config | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` env vars | OS `core_pattern` / `systemd-coredump` |\n| Analysis tool | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `lldb` / `gdb` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fefbf0fe-a097-4cd9-bd61-8c9d1e618b1c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist on this machine. That's expected — the user is asking for guidance, not necessarily running the app on this exact machine. Let me provide them with the diagnostic steps and configuration guidance directly.","outputTokens":754,"requestId":"1B83:1DE8C5:1068275:128BF1E:6A028867"},"id":"a41111fa-fd80-4c7b-b5c6-670af09ed598","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:55:04.135Z","parentId":"2f96eeb6-e5ac-4e1b-8647-277d7dd56e1f"}
